T Pumpy Concept Limited, Developers of Abuja-based T Pumpy Estate has reiterated her commitment to make more Nigerians house owners. The company, through its MD/CEO, Akintanyo Adaralegbe made this known while unfolding their plans for 2021 before the press during the weekend. Mr. Adaralegbe said T Pumpy is committed to see more Nigerians own their houses in 2021 at affordable rates.  According to him, “We are opening more estates across Abuja. At the moment, we have over 34 housing estates spread across the nation’s capital in areas such as Guzape, Wawa, Kwali, Karasana, Kuje, Lugbe, and more. “We are not stopping there. We intend to open new vistas this year. “Our commitment is to see more Nigerians own their houses in 2021 and we promise to do more.  “In 2020, despite the global lockdown occasioned by the outbreak of the coronavirus in the country, we gave Nigerians the opportunity to have their own properties through series of promos. “Also, in 2020, we opened the first of its kind, the children estate in Kwali. “This year, we will keep you guys in the media posted on our activities.”  Pumpy Concept Limited is a progressive property developer that prides itself on its proven track records, passion and commitment to deliver superior value in design, quality and services in our developments to our customers. Pumpy Concept is a registered company that deals majorly in the sales of lands and estate plots. The company has been in existence since 2009, and it’s totally committed to making its utmost contribution in the development process of our environment in the aforementioned areas, for the betterment of all Nigerians. The T-Pumpy Concept team has decades of providing industry-acclaimed off-site home design and construction. Whether you’re interested in a manufactured home or an innovative modular design, the T-Pumpy Concept team continues to deliver what home buyers are looking for in their new homes along with the quality construction they expect and deserve.  Cal